  "description": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          Import Adobe Illustrator (<span style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">.ai</span>) Files        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          Import Adobe Illustrator <code style=\"background-color:rgba(248,250,252,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(248,250,252,0.14);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:6px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;color:#f8fafc;\">.ai</code> files directly into Blender with full support for images, gradients, colors, and layer organization. This powerful add-on uses a bundled Inkscape installation to convert .ai files to SVG format, ensuring seamless integration with Blender's native SVG importer.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/5c2db093a09e1fefd0152d4531221a8d.png\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"><table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\"><tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">              </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">What It Does</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">What It Does</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          This add-on bridges the gap between Adobe Illustrator and Blender, allowing you to seamlessly import your vector artwork into Blender's 3D environment. Whether you're creating logos, illustrations, technical drawings, or graphic designs in Illustrator, you can now bring them directly into Blender for 3D visualization, animation, texturing, or further creative work.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\"><br></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Key Features</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 20px 0;\">Key Features</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 20px 0;\">\n<img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/d6cf660289eb999b87c3cfec9bebfb2a.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"><br>\n</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/3674fef630720716b7640149fb8a910f.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><br></div>              </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <table width=\"100%\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Zero External Dependencies</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Import .ai files without installing any additional software. The add-on includes a fully bundled Inkscape installation, so everything you need is included right out of the box.              </div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Comprehensive File Format Support</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Handles both modern PDF-based .ai files (Adobe Illustrator CS and later) and legacy PostScript-based .ai files (older versions), ensuring compatibility with files from various versions of Adobe Illustrator.              </div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Full Visual Fidelity</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Preserves embedded images, gradients, colors, and vector paths exactly as they appear in Illustrator. Your artwork maintains its visual integrity throughout the import process.</div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">                          </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Smart Layer Management</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Automatic layer offset feature prevents overlapping geometry by adding small Z-axis offsets based on layer order. This ensures each layer is properly separated in 3D space, making it easy to work with complex multi-layer designs.              </div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Enhanced Material Display</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Automatically enhances materials to better display colors and gradients in Blender's viewport. The add-on intelligently processes imported materials to ensure optimal visibility and rendering quality.              </div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Flexible Unit System</div>              <img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/033e05f2d591301c56898df8c7475853.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;width:100%;display:block;margin:15px 0;border-radius:8px;\">              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin-top:10px;\">                Supports multiple unit systems for accurate scaling:              </div>              <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">                <tbody>\n<tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Points (default) - AI/PDF standard (72 points = 1 inch)                  </td>                </tr>                <tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Millimeters (mm)                  </td>                </tr>                <tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Centimeters (cm)                  </td>                </tr>                <tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Meters (m)                  </td>                </tr>                <tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Inches                  </td>                </tr>                <tr>                  <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                    • Custom scale factor for precise control                  </td>                </tr>              </tbody>\n</table>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Streamlined Workflow</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Drag-and-drop support allows you to quickly import files by simply dragging them into Blender's 3D viewport. Batch import multiple files at once for efficient workflow.              </div>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:0 0 20px 0;\">              <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">✓ Advanced Image Processing</div>              <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">                Automatically extracts embedded images from .ai files and converts base64-encoded images to separate image files, ensuring proper texture handling in Blender.              </div>            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Use Cases</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Use Cases</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">\n<img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/a1143f0ce2d967fa78f5828d8fc5591e.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"><br>\n</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Logo Design to 3D: Bring your 2D logos into Blender and create stunning 3D versions            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Technical Drawings: Import technical illustrations and architectural plans for 3D modeling reference            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Graphic Design: Convert print designs into 3D assets for motion graphics and animation            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Texturing: Use Illustrator artwork as texture sources or reference for UV mapping            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Motion Graphics: Animate vector graphics imported from Illustrator            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Product Visualization: Import product designs and create realistic 3D renderings            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">How It Works</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">How It Works</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          The add-on uses a sophisticated conversion pipeline:        </div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              1. Detects and validates the .ai file format (PDF-based or PostScript-based)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              2. Uses bundled Inkscape to convert .ai to SVG format            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              3. Processes the SVG to extract embedded images and optimize structure            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              4. Imports the SVG using Blender's native SVG importer            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              5. Applies unit conversion and scaling based on your preferences            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              6. Enhances materials and applies layer offsets for optimal 3D organization            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Technical Details</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Technical Details</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          The plugin uses Inkscape's powerful conversion engine (bundled) to convert .ai files to SVG format, which is then imported into Blender using the built-in SVG importer. This ensures maximum compatibility and high-quality preservation.        </div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Compatible with Blender 3.0 and later            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Requires Blender's built-in SVG importer (enabled by default)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Supports both single and batch file imports            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Handles complex vector paths, bezier curves, and shapes            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Preserves color information and gradient definitions            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Automatic cleanup of temporary files after import            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Installation & Setup</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          Installation is straightforward - simply install the add-on through Blender's preferences, and you're ready to go. No additional configuration required. The bundled Inkscape is automatically detected and used. Advanced users can optionally specify a custom Inkscape path if needed.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Requirements</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Requirements</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Blender <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">3.0 or higher</strong>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Built-in SVG importer <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\"><code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">io_curve_svg</code></strong> enabled            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;line-height:1.75;text-align:center;\">          Perfect for designers, artists, and 3D professionals who want to seamlessly integrate their Adobe Illustrator workflow with Blender's powerful 3D capabilities. Whether you're working on branding projects, technical visualizations, or creative animations, this add-on provides the bridge you need between 2D vector graphics and 3D creation.        </div>      </td>    </tr>  </tbody></table>\n</div>",
  "documentation": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          Import Adobe Illustrator (<span style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">.ai</span>) Documentation        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          Complete guide to importing Adobe Illustrator files into Blender with full color, gradient, and layer preservation.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\"><br></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Overview</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Overview</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          This addon enables Blender to import CorelDRAW (.cdr) files while preserving colors, gradients, images, and layer structures. It converts CDR files to SVG format using Inkscape (bundled) and then imports them into Blender using the built-in SVG importer.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Installation</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">\n<img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/084b29b6f9611eacb2c09f48a16eb6b0.jpg\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"><br>\n</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">1.</strong> Download the addon zip file            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">2.</strong> Open Blender            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">3.</strong> Go to <code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">Edit > Preferences > Add-ons</code>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">4.</strong> Click \"Install...\" and select the zip file            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">5.</strong> Enable the addon by checking the checkbox next to \"Import CorelDRAW (.cdr) with Colors\"            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">6.</strong> Ensure the built-in \"Import-Export: Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)\" addon is enabled            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Requirements</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Requirements</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Blender <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">3.0 or higher</strong>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Built-in SVG importer <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\"><code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">io_curve_svg</code></strong> must be enabled            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • The addon includes a bundled Inkscape converter (no additional installation needed)            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Usage</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Usage</div>                <div style=\"font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:20px 0 10px 0;\">Importing Files</div>                <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Method 1: File Menu</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">1.</strong> Go to <code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">File > Import > CorelDRAW Graphics (.cdr)</code>            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">2.</strong> Select one or more CDR files            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">3.</strong> Configure import options in the dialog            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">4.</strong> Click \"Import CDR File\"            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Method 2: Drag and Drop</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">1.</strong> Drag a CDR file into Blender's 3D Viewport            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">2.</strong> Configure import options in the dialog that appears            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">3.</strong> Click \"OK\" to import            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>        <div style=\"font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:20px 0 10px 0;\">Import Options</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:8px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Enhance Material Display:</strong> Automatically enhances materials to better display colors and gradients in the viewport            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:8px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Layer Offset:</strong> Adds small Z-axis offsets based on layer order to prevent overlapping            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:8px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Offset Distance:</strong> Sets the Z-axis offset distance between layers (default: 0.001)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:8px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Import Units:</strong> Choose the unit system for imported files:            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0 4px 20px;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Millimeters (mm)</strong> - Default, commonly used in CDR files            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0 4px 20px;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Centimeters (cm)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0 4px 20px;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Meters (m)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0 4px 20px;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Inches            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0 4px 20px;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Points (72 points = 1 inch)            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:8px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Custom Scale:</strong> Custom scale factor (when custom unit is selected)            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Preferences</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Preferences</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Access via <code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">Edit > Preferences > Add-ons > Import CorelDRAW (.cdr) with Colors</code>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 8px 0;\">Default Import Options:</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Enhance Material Display:</strong> Enable/disable automatic material enhancement            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">Import Units:</strong> Set default unit system for imports            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Features</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Features</div>                <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Color Preservation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Colors from CDR files are preserved and automatically enhanced for optimal display in Blender. The addon creates emission shaders to ensure colors are visible in both viewport and render.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Gradient Support</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Gradients are preserved during import and displayed correctly in Blender. The addon enhances gradient materials for better visibility.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Image Import</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Embedded images in CDR files are automatically extracted from base64 encoding and imported as separate image assets. Images are stored in a temporary directory during conversion and properly referenced in the imported SVG.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Layer Offset</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          To prevent layers from overlapping, the addon can automatically apply small Z-axis offsets based on layer order. This ensures each layer is slightly separated in 3D space.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Batch Import</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Import multiple CDR files at once. All files will use the same import settings, and you'll receive a summary of imported objects and images.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">Unit Conversion</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          The addon supports multiple unit systems and automatically converts CDR units to Blender units (meters). This ensures accurate scaling of imported graphics.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Troubleshooting</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Troubleshooting</div>                <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">ISSUE: \"Parser not found\" error</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">SOLUTION:</strong> Ensure the addon is properly installed. The bundled Inkscape converter should be included in the Inkscape folder.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">ISSUE: \"Please enable SVG importer\" error</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">SOLUTION:</strong> Go to <code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;\">Edit > Preferences > Add-ons</code> and enable \"Import-Export: Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)\".        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">ISSUE: Colors not displaying correctly</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">SOLUTION:</strong> Enable \"Enhance Material Display\" in import options or preferences. This ensures colors are visible in the viewport.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">ISSUE: Layers overlapping</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">SOLUTION:</strong> Enable \"Layer Offset\" in import options to automatically separate layers on the Z-axis.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:16px 0 8px 0;\">ISSUE: Imported objects are too large/small</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;font-weight:700;\">SOLUTION:</strong> Adjust the \"Import Units\" setting to match the unit system used in your CDR file. CDR files typically use millimeters.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Technical Details</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Technical Details</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • The addon uses Inkscape's command-line interface to convert CDR to SVG            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • SVG files are temporarily created during import and cleaned up afterward            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Base64-encoded images are extracted and saved as separate files            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Material nodes are automatically created and enhanced for better display            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • The addon supports Blender 3.0+ and uses modern Python features            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Limitations</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Limitations</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Complex CDR features may not be fully supported            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Some CDR-specific effects may be simplified during conversion            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Very large files may take longer to process            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Support</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Support</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          For issues, questions, or feature requests, please refer to the addon's support channels.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Version History</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Version History</div>        <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 8px 0;\">v0.2.0 - Current version</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:10px 0;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Full English localization            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Enhanced material display            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Layer offset support            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Multiple unit systems            </td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:4px 0;font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">              • Batch import